pan class=title>   Re: Congratulations to Resolution Members</span><hr size=1> I so knew this was going to happen.<br><br>/em glances upward at Shintou's reply.<br><br>Okay.  This is going to be a running issue if something isn't done about it now.  So, in the interest of peace on this board, let me form a sort of loose general policy on this stuff right now.<br><br>If you want to boast, either on your own or someone else's behalf, about the big thing you just killed and the great loot you scored, take it to the soapbox.  Why?  Because it is going to attract fire.  A lot of people feel it doesn't belong on this board at all.  And to a large extent, as a moderator and as an individual (I'll be clear on that point) I find myself in agreement with that viewpoint.<br><br>There is certainly nothing wrong with the end game, or with aspiring to great accomplishments.  More power to those who are persuing such things.  But this board isn't the place to bring news of such accomplishments.  Enjoy it in private, and with your friends, the same way everyone else enjoys their accomplishments (whatever they may be) in Norrath.<br><br>I'm moving this to the Soapbox rather than locking it entirely because I don't want to be an ogre (appologies to real ogres) about this right off the bat.  I am fairly certain I'm acting in the best interests and according to the general wishes of the board community here, but I won't know for sure unless this issue is left open for discussion.  So here it is; discuss it.  Perhaps if someone asked her Jaxy might be persuaded to put up a board for these sorts of accomplishments.  But I really don't think the majority of the people would frequent it.  Because I think the majority of the people who come here have their primary interest in other matters.<br><br>Hope this is taken well, and in the spirit in which it was intended.  And congradulations, Coinfist, on a successful raid, and on all the phat lewt.  Yes, I said phat lewt.  After all, that is what you are boasting about, isn't it?<br><br>Valquiss <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uanklesdirtyfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ankles Dirtyfoot</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_magentaspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mudslingin' Admin</span><br>  Posts: 465<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/26/02 6:59:28 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Congratulations to Resolution Members</span><hr size=1> Good job guys :)<br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> k thx ankles for letting us know Lodi was up. here, have the map piece! gratz!</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p><font face="arial" size="-1" color="black"><b>Ankles Dirtyfoot</font><font face="arial" size="-1"> &lt;<a href="http://www.geocities.com/starspunguild">Starspun</a>&gt;<br></b><i>Black-soled, bow-slingin' hippie</i><br>Misbehaving for 38 summers<br>Hopelessly devoted to Fayd Dirtyfoot</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujadia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jadia</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_magentaspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Jadia Cookiecutter<br>Distributor of fine cookies</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/26/02 7:07:30 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://jadia.freeservers.com/images/jadiakazoo.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Congratulations to Resolution Members</span><hr size=1> BAH! <b