p align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Congratulations to Resolution Members</span><hr size=1> oh and one other thing for you Valquiss<br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showMessage?topicID=724.topic">pub94.ezboard.com/ffirion...=724.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>Those are the rules of this board, and the ones you are supposed to follow as a mod. So please, don't go adding rules that YOU see fit without at least running it by Jaxy.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/26/02 8:23:09 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_tongue.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Congratulations to Resolution Members</span><hr size=1> I'm definitely not one of the uber-anythings nor do I ever expect to be.... I'm quite the opposite, just another lame newbie as far as the server is concered....<br><br>But I'm gonna have to go with Jadia here.... my congrats to Resolution. I don't know any of you in Resolution, nor do I know how you play the game. Nor do I really care. But when people or guilds on this server start reaching milestones.... it took a lot of effort to get there. And that should be something that the ENTIRE Firiona Vie server should be proud of because it gives our entire server some bragging rights in the eyes of the rest of the EQ world. At the very least I'm going to give recognition for that. <br><br>But judging from Shintou's remark... I think they are being singled out BECAUSE they are perceived as one of the powergamer guilds.... so that means we should snub them with a double standard and refuse them a sincere congratulation?? <br><br>Sorry... I dont believe in double standards. Unless some person or guild deserves to be on my shitlist (and at the moment there is nothing on my list) -- then I will give everyone on this server the benefit of the doubt regardless of what their style of play is.... be they hard core role player or relaxed casual RPer, or relaxed casual newbie gamer, or even a powergaming uber guild (as long as it's an uber guild that has manners and class and respects the RPers). <br><br>I do like what Val suggested... maybe in the future, some kind of area reserved for congrats/kudos and achievements for all guilds and members of this server. That way, all the WOOT this and WOOT that and WOOT WE KILLED TUNARE types of threads will be shoved specifically on that area of the forum. If people want to read those threads and congratulate them, they will. If people like Shintou dont want to see such congratulatory threads, then simply stay away from it. Given the current situation, I agree with Val that moving it over here was the next best thing. <br><br>This entire forum should belong to the entire FV community... and that means all kinds. We have all kinds, not just the hard core role players. As much as some people wish the powergamers would just die and disappear from the server.... sorry, I don't see that ever happening.  <br><br>People, learn to get along... or at least be civil to one another. Otherwise, I see a huge huge polarization going to happen months later down the line. It will tear our server apart and divide us into opposing camps....everyone knows it's already a small server, small in numbers. I doubt we can afford that. <br><br>this necromancer midget will step down from the podium now... <br><br>/smirk<br>/pickpockets Jadia's legendary cookies and runs off <br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A> at: 1/26/02 8:28:16 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> 